- title("Help Us Open Government")

%p OpenGovernment is a free and open-source website for government transparency at the state and local levels. We're a non-profit and non-partisan public resource based on OpenCongress.org, the most-visited site for tracking the U.S. Congress.

%p This beta version of OpenGovernment connects you with the legislatures of five states: California, Louisiana, Maryland, Texas, and Wisconsin. We have a good start, but we need more resources to roll out OpenGovernment to all 50 U.S. states and beyond.  

%p Want to see a version of OpenGovernment for your state and city, and make this free public resource even better?  <strong>Help us grow!</strong> 

%p First, join our e-mail list to stay in touch:

%form(action="http://crm.ppolitics.org/civicrm/mailing/subscribe" method="post")
